comments: Curry (GSW) legally contests Rivers' (DEN) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
During the rebound, Looney (GSW) and Jokic (DEN) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Wiggins (GSW) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Looney (GSW) briefly grasps and immediately releases Jokic's (DEN) jersey in the post. The contact is marginal and does not affect Jokic's SQBR on his way to the basket.
Looney (GSW) does not get ball height and makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) wrist, which affects his shot near the basket.
Payton II (GSW) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.

Wiggins (GSW) moves alongside of Barton (DEN) with his arm collapsed against his body while his other arm is vertical when he makes clean ball contact to block the shot. Any contact to Barton's head as he moves toward the basket is deemed marginal.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Payton II (GSW) extends his arms out slightly and then brings them into a vertical position as he absorbs the contact from Barton (DEN) on his driving shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (GSW) makes clean ball contact on his dislodge attempt during Barton's (DEN) putback attempt at the basket.
Wiggins (GSW) avoids making contact with Barton's (DEN) arm during his putback shot attempt at the basket.
Looney (GSW) and Barton (DEN) reach for the loose ball and any contact on the tip-shot is deemed incidental.
Looney (GSW) establishes himself in a screening position in Rivers' (DEN) path and absorbs the contact on the pick.
After tipping the rebound, Wiggins (GSW) grabs Barton's (DEN) arm and the contact affects his ability to secure the rebound.
Wiggins (GSW) rests his hands on Rivers' (DEN) back and the contact is marginal as he does not extend them to get to the pass.
During the errant pass by Jokic (DEN), Wiggins (GSW) maintains a legal guarding position on Barton (DEN) off-ball.
Porter Jr. (GSW) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Porter Jr. (GSW) slips the contact with Campazzo (DEN) after passing the ball at the end of his drive.
Jokic (DEN) maintains a legal guarding position and cleanly blocks the shot during the play at the basket by Kuminga (GSW).
Porter Jr. (GSW) attempts to steal the ball and marginal contact occurs with Campazzo's (DEN) side, which does not affect his SQBR.
Looney (GSW) and Jokic (DEN) engage and disengage while rebounding.
During the inbound, Curry (GSW) and Jokic (DEN) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Wiggins (GSW) commits a take foul on Campazzo (DEN).
Green (DEN) legally contests Iguodala's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
